category.name: Camping & Hiking
category.description: Connect with Mother Nature by spending time outdoors hiking and camping. Hiking involves walking outdoors on a trail or path for recreational purposes. Hiking is a great form of exercise and can help revitalize your mind and body. People who work in stuffy offices and follow a sedentary lifestyle, must go hiking or camping in order to break free from their normal everyday routine. Camping involves staying overnight at the campsite either in a tent or a caravan. These campsites are normally far from cities and found in national or state parks. Hiking and camping can teach respect for nature, self confidence, teamwork and the ability to think on your feet. The equipment needed while camping have to be lightweight, compact, durable and most importantly useful during your trip. Hiking has many health benefits like improving your endurance and stamina from walking long distances.

category.name: Cycling
category.description: Cycling is a very efficient and cost effective way to travel short to medium distances without polluting the environment. Cycling is defined as the use of bicycle for sport, transport and recreation. With the number of cycles in the world crossing a billion, they have become a popular mode of transportation in many countries. There are many benefits to riding a cycle instead of using your motor car or bike. If you care about the environment and want to reduce your carbon footprint, riding a cycle is for you. A cycle does not burn fossil fuel to work and therefore does not create any air or noise pollution. You can avoid the traffic congestions on the road and cycle past them on the sidewalk to reach your destination quicker in cities. Cycles offer greater maneuverability and can be parked anywhere by chaining it to a fixed object.

category.name: Running
category.description: Running is an excellent way to get in shape without joining a gym and spending much money. You can run in a park, on a treadmill or simply around the block. Running can be quite invigorating and helps relax your mind. Depending on the weather, wear the appropriate clothes to enhance your running experience. Wear the right socks that help absorb moisture from your feet and ensure the shoes you use is also specifically designed for running. Slowly increase the distance you run over time to see better results. Running the same route everyday might get boring, so trying other routes will make it interesting. You can run alone by listening to your favorite music, or you can make it more fun by running with friends who also want to get fit. Encourage your running habits by rewarding yourself with running gear and equipment to make it even more fun to get in shape.

category.name: Basketball
category.description: Basketball is one of the most exciting team sports played with fast paced action and lots of scoring opportunities. Two teams of 5 players each compete against each other to score points by dribbling and shooting the ball through the opposite team's basket. If a player shoots a basket from inside the three-point line, he score 2 points, but if he scores from outside the three-point line, 3 points are added to the total score. Advance on the court by running or walking while dribbling the ball or pass the ball to your teammates in order to create scoring opportunities. There are specialized shots in basketball known as the lay-up, jump-shot, slam dunk, alley-oop, one-handed underhand shot and the hook shot. A free throw is awarded by a referee to a player who has been fouled by an opponent.

category.name: Cricket
category.description: Cricket is the most popular sport in India with millions of fans for the Indian Cricket Team. This game is played at different levels starting from school level tournaments all the way up to the international level tournaments. Sachin Tendulkar is India's most famous batsman and the inspiration for many a young batsman aspiring to touch the sky. Cricket is a game of skill and physical ability with players having to play for long hours depending on the game format. There are three main formats in cricket which are the limited overs 20Twenty format, limited 50 over one-day format and the unlimited overs Test format played over 5 days. Cricket originated in England and has become popular in countries like Pakistan, Sri Lanka, Australia, South Africa and West Indies.

category.name: Footboll
category.description: Football is an International game that is played all over the world and it is popular with people of all ages. Both men and women play this sport competitively with tournaments starting at the school level all the way up to the World Cup level. Football is an easy game to learn and it comes with many health benefits. Football helps improve your stamina and endurance as you have to run a lot during the game to maintain control of the ball. A football team consists of 11 players, playing in different positions such as forward strikers, midfielders, defenders and a goalkeeper. Only the goalkeeper is allowed to touch the ball with his hands, while all the other players are only allowed to kick the ball. The objective of the game is to kick the ball into the opposing team's goal post. Football requires dedication and practice to play as a team.

category.name: Cardiac Surgery
category.description:
The Dharam Vira Heart Centre was inaugurated on 6th February, 1999 by then President of India Mr. K. R. Narayanan.

Besides being a hub of modern technology, the centre is renowned for its humane touch, keeping in view the critical condition of the patients.

Departments of Cardiac Surgery India and Cardiac Anesthesia at the Dharamvira Heart Centre are a composite unit with State of the art equipment to handle open-heart adult and paediatric surgeries in its two operation theatres.

The center caters to a wide spectrum of cardiac cases from neonates to adults and from the routine to the very complicated. At present the department is doing following procedures regularly.

Coronary artery bypass surgery including total arterial revascularisation.

Beating heart bypass surgery (OPCAB/Minimally invasive/Key hole).

Valve replacement/repair

Congenital heart operation which includes cynotic as well as acynotic congenital heart disease.

Closed heart operations

Aortic Arch replacement and repair surgeries.

Carotid artery surgeries.
The cardiac surgeons India at DVHC are well versed in the art and fine nuances of coronary artery bypass surgery, especially total arterial revascularisation, redo beating heart bypass surgeries and minimally invasive (key hole) surgeries. In last 7 years since the inception of the department, over 4000 surgeries have been done.

We had the previous five years witness a conceptual change in the approach to coronary artery bypass surgery. The very concept of beating heart surgery was taken to newer heights, when department attained a very high percentage of total arterial grafts and an amazingly low mortality and morbidity rate amongst our patients. Infact the success of our surgical programme, places Sir Ganga Ram Hospital amongst the better institutions, not only at the national level, but also internationally.

One of the offshoot of aggressive cardiological intervention is that now we are doing Coronary Surgeries on patients with a far greater severity of disease than seen earlier and with a host of associated medical problems. For us this has translated into a far more demanding surgical and anaesthetic challenges and needless to say success equally so rewarding.

General cardiology services are available through consultant cardiologists and associates in Cardiology Treatment India

The overall mortality has come steadily down from 3.8% in 2001 to 1.8% in 2002, 1.1% in 2003 and 0.7% in 2005. Infact the last 250 Open Heart/ CABG have been free of any mortality.

Along side surgical programs, the department gives equal importance to the academics. A very aggressive teaching programme has been pursued for the DNB candidates and visiting medical personnel, interested in our techniques. Conferences and workshop with excellent presentations and award winning papers have been main stay of our presence on the academic front at the national level.

The care of treatment provided is as good as the best in anywhere in the world

category.name: Chest Medicine
category.description:
The speciality of Chest Medicine deals with a gamut of diseases that involve the lungs, airways, mediastinum, pleura, diaphragm and the chest wall. Not only thoracic, but disorders that affect the breathing indirectly like neuromuscular disorders, sleep disorders are also part of the speciality.


The burden of chest diseases is increasing with growing urbanization, pollution and due to harmful effects of smoking. The diseases that we encounter commonly in our population for which Chest Medicine services are required are Asthma, Bronchiectasis, Tuberculosis, Pneumonias, Chest traumas, Pneumothorax, Pleural effusions, Mediastinal lymph adenopathy, Lung cancer, Sleep disorders, Allergies, and Respiratory failure due to various causes.


The department of Chest Medicine has been functional at Sir Ganga Ram Hospital since 1993. It provides all that is necessary for high quality care of patients, viz. excellent manpower resources in its consultants and post graduate residents, state-of-the-art equipment required for diagnosis and treatment of respiratory diseases, a humane approach combined with total dedication and academic activities to always remain abreast with the latest developments in the field of respiratory medicine.


Our department is well equipped to deal with preventive, diagnostic, therapeutic, emergency and rehabilitative aspects of Chest Medicine to provide quality and comprehensive care for our patients which is comparable to best in the world.


One of the major highlights is our foray in recent years into interventional pulmonology which is likely to become a super speciality in the coming future. We are proud of our setup of Endobronchial ultrasound (EBUS), which is the first of its kind in the country which offers both linear and radial EBUS facilities. We have performed more than 1200 EBUS procedures in the last 3 years, which is by far the highest by any centre in the country. Another highlight of the department is the dedicated Respiratory High Dependency Unit (HDU) fully equipped with invasive and non-invasive ventilators and hemodynamic monitoring.
